						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up before the Sakalēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kōṭa: [Gaṇapatidēva].</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 117[8], Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Records the remission of the tax due from the servants of the temple at Māmaṁḍala by Gaṇapamadēvi for the merit of her father Gaṇapadēva Mahārāja.</p>						

